<subSubSection id="1DB16551103E682FFF19F814E7552026" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="551436DA103E682FFF19F814E7552026" blockId="6.[136,1452,780,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFF19F814E3732377" bold="true" box="[189,315,1369,1395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFEFBF817E0042377" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,588,1370,1396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFEFBF817E0042377" box="[351,588,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFD6FF817E0A82370" box="[715,736,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFCE6F817E6022370" authorityName="Clarke" authorityYear="1876" box="[834,1098,1370,1396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Strictae">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFCE6F817E1FC2370" box="[834,948,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFC57F817E6022370" box="[1011,1098,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Strictae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its pinnately dentate leaves and solitary capitula. This species is distinct in its outer pappus plumose. 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFB81F830E75D2392" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1061,1301,1405,1431]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFB81F830E75D2392" box="[1061,1301,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFF5EF8D2E0AE23BD" authority="Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang" authorityName="Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang" box="[250,742,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFF5EF8D2E3E723BD" box="[250,431,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B103E682FFD52F8D2E1A323BE" author="Chen, Y. L. &amp; Liang, S. Y. &amp; Pan, K. Y." box="[758,1003,1439,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" pagination="85 - 106" refId="ref6721" refString="Chen, Y. L., Liang, S. Y. &amp; Pan, K. Y. (1981) Taxa nova compositarum e flora Xizangensi (Tibetica). Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 19 (1): 85 - 106." type="journal article" year="1981">
Chen 
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFC9EF8EDE13A23BD" box="[826,882,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">et al.</emphasis>
1981: 105
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFB8FF8D2E03023D8" authority="(Lindley ex Royle 1835: 251) Wallich ex Candolle (1838: 532)" authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityPageNumber="532" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Lindley ex Royle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="251" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taraxacifolia">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFB8FF8D2E69023BD" box="[1067,1240,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. taraxacifolia</emphasis>
(Lindley ex 
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B103E682FFACCF8D2E2B223D8" author="Royle, J. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="197" refId="ref7534" refString="Royle, J. F. (1835) Illustrations of the Botany and other Branches of the Natural History of the Himalayan Mountains, and the Flora of Cashmere, vol. 1. Wm. H. Allen and Co., London, 472 pp." type="book" year="1835">Royle 1835: 251</bibRefCitation>
) Wallich ex 
<bibRefCitation id="313A4B2B103E682FFE2CF88CE03023D8" author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[392,632,1473,1500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" refId="ref6692" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1838) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, vol. 6. Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 687 pp." type="book" year="1838">Candolle (1838: 532)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its leaf shape. However 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFC0EF88FE67423DF" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[938,1084,1474,1500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFC0EF88FE67423DF" box="[938,1084,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in its usually stemless habit, caudex numerous branched, leaves sessile and linear-lanceolate, margin denate, capitula usually smaller, outer pappus plumose. A comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFDAFFB44E0D42026" authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[523,668,1545,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFDAFFB44E0D42026" box="[523,668,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFD0EFB44E1162026" box="[682,862,1545,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFD0EFB44E1162026" box="[682,862,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92AB4D59103E682FFC31FB44E60A2026" authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Lindley ex Royle" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[917,1090,1544,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taraxacifolia">
<emphasis id="67DFEAC8103E682FFC31FB44E60A2026" box="[917,1090,1544,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. taraxacifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given in 
<tableCitation id="18290361103E682FFB60FB45E7552026" box="[1220,1309,1544,1570]" captionStart-0="TABLE 4" captionStart-1="TABLE 5" captionStartId-0="6.[136,224,1618,1642]" captionStartId-1="8.[136,224,1573,1597]" captionText-0="TABLE 4. Comparison of Saussurea pagriensis, S. purpurascens and S. taraxacifolia." captionText-1="TABLE 5. Comparison of Saussurea bhutanensis, S. columnaris and S. durgae." pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Table 4.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
